DispatchPtr

getN

public java.lang.Object getN(java.lang.String prop,
                             java.lang.Object[] indexes)
                      throws COMException
For getting a property identified by the property name and multiple index'es. Does not necessarely have to be integers - it depends on how the native get-method interprets the indexes.

One scenario where this can be used, is eg. for retriving the value of a single cell in a spreadsheet, where two "indexes" (row and column) are needed for identifying the cell.

See Variant.readObject(LittleEndianInputStream) for further information about the typeconversion that takes place when converting the native property value to a java type.

Parameters:
prop - the name of the property.
indexes - the parameters to pass to the the native property get method.
Returns:
the value of the property.
Throws:
COMException - if no such property, or if the native code failed in any other way.
java.lang.NullPointerException - if prop is null.

                 java.lang.Object val)
          throws COMException
For setting a new value for a property identified by the property name and multiple index'es. Does not necessarely have to be integers - it depends on how the native put-method interprets the indexes.

One scenario where this can be used, is eg. for setting the value of a single cell in a spreadsheet, where two "indexes" (row and column) are needed for identifying the cell.

The Variant.writeObject(Object, LittleEndianOutputStream) should be consulted for further information about what type of object should be passed as value.

Parameters:
prop - the name of the property.
indexes - the indexes to pass to the the native property put method.
val - the new value of the property.
Throws:
COMException - if no such property, or if the native code failed in any other way.
